  "text": "The high concentration of tear albumin in our patient is another interesting finding. Albumin, a major protein in the serum, is found in low concentrations in tears, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and reports have shown varied tear albumin concentrations, even in normal subjects, and increased tear albumin levels in patients with dry eye. [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] The tear albumin concentration in our patient was more than double of that in controls and further increased with punctal occlusion, supporting the diagnosis of congenital alacrima and shedding light on the efficacy of punctal occlusion.",
